@esquerra
title: Republican Left of Catalonia (ERC)
face-image: img/parties/logo_erc.svg

**Republican Left of Catalonia - ERC**

The left-wing republican party advocates for Catalan independence, socialism, and anti-austerity measures. Formed in 1931, it endured Franco's dictatorship and re-emerged post-1975. It governed in as part of the 2003-2010 tripartite coalition with PSC and ICV-EUiA but lost support after compromising for governance, poor economic leadership, and the failed new charter of autonomy. Now in 2012 is seems to be the main beneficiary of the growing independence sentiment, pushing for a referendum on self-determination.

- @esquerra_2: Yes, we'll be the left of a new country!
- @party_selection: No, select a different party.


@esquerra_2
